Little update 0.6.2

- Hook execution errors (IOError) are now `warning` instead of `error`.
- Increased ReadySet service timeout for long-running hooks.
- Increased default window size.

- Added Drag & Drop for reordering input sources.
- Added layout preview dialog.
- Added option to select layout switch combination (Alt+Shift, Ctrl+Shift, Caps Lock).
- Used system `xkb-model` instead of hardcoded value.
- Fixed crash when dropping an item on itself.

- Used standard `GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_LEFT_RIGHT` transition.

- Added pre-commit hooks for Vala and Blueprint linting.

- Moved `gnome-initial-setup` conflict to `gdm` subpackage.
